title: Pacific Raceways Women's Road Racing Skills Clinic
description:
Women’s Clinic & Race Day, Feb. 25th, 2017; 9:00AM Registration & Check-in; Clinic from 9:30AM - 12:30PM; Racing from 1pm; Location: Pacific Raceways 

Men’s Clinic & Race Day, Feb. 25th, 2017; 2:30PM Registration & Check-in; Clinic from 3.00PM; Racing at 4.15PM
course:
Women: Join other female cyclists for a one day road racing skills and simulation racing clinic, with optional afternoon sanctioned racing. This clinic is intended for new racers to learn what it takes to race on the road and come away with more confidence through practice and race simulations. Experienced Cat 4 women, and Cat 3 women are also encouraged to attend and brush up on skills plus learn some new ones. Come out to learn a variety of road racing skills: -- Cornering -- Contact/bumping -- Sprinting -- Pack riding & pacelining. Located in Kent, Pacific Raceways is a car race track where you can learn in a safe, controlled environment. We rent out the track for the day, so you can practice without cars in your way.*
 
Men: this year we are delighted to also offer beginner men the opportunity to build skills and race following the women’s racing program. *
registration: A 2017 USA Cycling annual license is required or you will need to purchase a one day license for $10 (new racers can purchase a one day license via the USA Cycling website (preferred) or on-site)
directions: Pacific Raceways 31001 144th Ave SE, Kent, WA 98042. Google map for directions: https://goo.gl/maps/ZVKhz9EAaUP2

title: The Ridge Circuit Race and TT #2
The Ridge Circuit Race and TT
Spokane Festival of Speed Bicycle Road Race
Taco Time Volunteer Park Criterium
description: This is the 50th anniversary of the Volunteer Park Criterium sponsored by Taco Time NW Restaurants and the Taco Time Cycling Team.  Continuous racing starting at 11:00am and ending at 7:00pm.
course: The course is a 0.7 of a mile closed loop paved road inside the park with sweeping corners and a gradual climb to the finish line.  The start/finish line is in front of the Seattle Asian Art Museum.
registration: Registration opens March 1, 2017.  Registration information is on the USA Cycling website.  Register for a second race is $25.00 on the day of the race.
notes:
Warmup areas are located near the finish line.  The course will not be open for warmup until after 10:30am to give time to remove moss for the lower road way. 
*We will offer separate scoring for the collegiate racers and prizes three deep* Collegiate prizes are Cactus Cards three deep, $75.00, $50.00,  and $25.00
directions: 1400 East Prospect is at the North end of Capitol Hill in Seattle.  Ample street parking is available south and east of the park.

title: Hedrick Cycles Echo Series; River Road Time Trial
Proctor/Tacoma Criterium/Masters WSBA Criterium Championship
description: The Proctor Station/Tacoma Criterium (previously know as the Tacoma Twilight)  Will again be hosting the WSBA Master Men/Women Criteruim Championships.  Medals and winners Jersey's will be awarded to all qualifying field winners at the end of each respective race.  Only licensed USAC riders are welcome to participate but only WSBA active WSBA members will be eligible for championship honors.  In addition this is the final race in the new Cascade Criterium Points Series.  Final category winners will be jersey's will be awarded at the conclusion of the respective fields.  For more information see series details on FB
course: We will be returning to the very popular 2014 4 corner counterclockwise coarse around Mason Middle School.  This .7ml route has deep corners on near perfect surface with a short but quickly rising finish!  Should provide for very fast racing.
registration: Early bird registration of $30 ends on June 15th.  $35 until close of online registration on July 14th and $40 day of.  Anyone buying either a one day or annual license will be given a $15 discount on their first race.  2016 Tacoma Twilight field winners will again race for free but only with online pre registration.  Contact Scott for your discount code, tacomabikeracing253@gmail.com
notes: All USAC and WSBA rules will strictly enforced.  Medical and neutral services will be provided on site.  Please observe all neighborhood parking regulations and remember we are invited guest's.  Team and individual tents may be placed on the inside of the race coarse enclose around the middle school.
directions: Exit I-5 onto Hwy 16 to 6th Ave east (exit #3) and proceed to Proctor Ave.  Turn left to the Proctor District (26th and Proctor.  Registration will be at the start/finish area near 28th and Madison Ave.

title: 2017 Gig Harbor Circuit Race
description: 2017 Gig Harbor Circuit Race presented by Gig Harbor Velo
course: The course is a 4 mile circuit with 285 feet of climbing per lap and with one hill that climbs 250 feet in approximately 3/4 of a mile. Pavement is good either black top or chip seal.
registration:
Kopachuck Middle School at 10414 56th St NW Gig Harbor. Registration area will be
clearly marked at each race. Registration will close 20 minutes before the start of your Category's race. USA
Cycling license required to race. One day license for category 5 men and 5 women is $10 and available at the
race. All other categories must have an USA Cycling annual license ($70) which can be purchased at www.usacycling.org (not for sale at the race).
notes:
WSBA numbers will be used and can be purchased at www.wsbaracing.com. Rental numbers
will be available at the race for a $10 rental fee (of which $5 is refundable). For out-of-state riders there is no fee to rent a number just a $5 deposit. Race numbers should be placed on the right side and please use your frame
number.
directions: Exit Hwy 16 at Wollochet Dr NW/City Center. Continue straight onto Stinson Rd. Turn left on Rosedale St NW. Turn left on Ray Nash Dr NW. Ray Nash turns into Kopachuck Dr. Staging is at Kopachuck Middle School.

title: NWCXCUP Race #5
description: NW CX CUP #5 - Kayak Point Cross
course: Cyclocross at a golf course! Do we need to say more. This course will be a roller coaster ride with hair raising descents and a “Koppenbergcross” climb. The big questions? How will your “driving” be in the Range.
notes:
We will be scoring with the timing chips used at MFG Cyclocross and *Cross Revolution. If you have raced either of these series please bring your current chip.

*All rider will need to check-in at Registration on race day.
directions:
From I-5 South: Take Exit #199 for Marysville / Tulalip. Turn Left onto 4th St and continue onto Marine Drive Follow for 12 Miles. Turn Right onto Kayak Point Road. Take the first Left onto 156th St NW. Kayak Point Golf Course entrance will be on the Left in 1/2 mile.

From I-5 North or South: Take Exit #202 for 116st St NE. Head West on 116st St NE (Left from South, Right from North). Turn Right at traffic light onto Quil Ceda Blvd. At the traffic circle, continue North on 34th Ave NE. At the traffic light, turn Left onto 136th St NE / Firetrail Road. Continue for 10 Miles. Becomes 140th St NE then becomes Kayak Point Road. There are brown Kayak Point signs along the way. At the bottom of the hill, turn Right onto 156th St NW. Kayak Point Golf Course entrance will be on the Left in 1/2 mile

Parking Fee: $5 per car.
